vllm-gfx1201
============

This project packages and lightly extends a large body of other people's work.
It would not exist without the following. Please preserve this NOTICE and the
upstream licenses in any redistribution.

The ONLY original contributions in this repository are:
  - the gfx1201 (RDNA4) enablement edits to vLLM / aiter / flash-attention,
  - the Docker build/inject packaging and compose profiles, and
  - the W4A8-FP8-WMMA MoE kernel (w4a8_fp8_wmma/).
Everything else is upstream, credited below.

Upstream projects and people
----------------------------
- The base image — tcclaviger/vllm22:dev (@tcclaviger), the collaborator's
  tuned-attention vLLM 0.22.69 build for RDNA4 (gfx1201): ROCm 7.2.1, torch 2.10,
  Python 3.12. The combined image is `FROM` this base, and almost everything runs
  here: the serving engine, the RDNA4-tuned attention (the collaborator built the
  entire attention half independently), and the RXF ("Rotated eXtra Fast") W4A8
  quant path (successor to RFP458). aiter and flash-attention are vendored inside
  this base too (see below).
- vLLM — vllm-project/vllm (Apache-2.0). The serving engine, shipped by the base
  image (vLLM 0.22.69). Our changes are a small ROCm platform-enablement edit plus
  the moe_wna16 tp_size fix (a generic upstream bug — owed back as a PR; see
  patches/upstream/). Thanks to @micah and the ROCm vLLM team.
- AMD aiter — ROCm/aiter (MIT/Apache) — and Dao-AILab flash-attention
  (Dao-AILab/flash-attention, BSD-3-Clause) with ROCm Composable Kernel
  (ROCm/composable_kernel, MIT) as the CK FMHA backend. These come from the base
  image. The five A8W8 GEMM config JSONs originate from @carhuang's
  `carhuang/gfx1201_silu_and_mul_and_a8w8_configs_rebased` branch. Thanks to @tridao.
- AMD ROCm / TheRock — the base of the *retired* wheel-distribution path, which
  built three gfx1201 wheels (vLLM / aiter / flash-attention) from source against
  AMD's TheRock (rocm/vllm-dev:nightly-therock714, ROCm 7.14) and the torch/triton
  nightlies. That path is archived on `archive/aiter-wheel-distribution`; the
  current stack no longer uses it (the base image above supersedes it).
- tilelang — the Qwen3_5Moe linear-attention (MHC) kernel path (upstream
  integration PR #43679).
- @kyuz0 — prior gfx1201 vLLM / ROCm-on-RDNA4 containers and PRs (e.g. the ViT
  attention-backend fix) that informed this enablement.
- cyankiwi — the AWQ-INT4 quantized models we run and benchmark
  (Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-AWQ-4bit, Mellum2-12B-A2.5B). The Qwen team for the base
  models.
- The gfx1151 sibling project (vllm-awq4-qwen) — the repository structure,
  compose, and README template, and the RDNA3.5 wave32 kernel-design lineage the
  W4A8 kernel was scaffolded from.
